### The mechanism contrast (substantive lesson)

Two theorems on float lattice structure can have very different scope properties depending on which mechanism their proofs use:

| Theorem | Mechanism | Subnormal | Format-agnostic? |
|---|---|---|---|
| **Conjecture C** | Scaling invariance (`R_above(m) = mantissa · 2^m` for fixed mantissa) | Breaks | Format-specific (different mantissa pattern per format) |
| **BACL (unified)** | Binade spacing (every float is `N · ulp` for integer N) | Holds | Format-agnostic |

When freezing a sub-result as "open," name the specific mechanism that would fail under the hypothesis violation. If no specific mechanism is identified, the freeze may be over-conservative — as the original BACL_subnormal freeze was.

